headline: A Look At Hormel Foods (HRL) Valuation After Guidance Hike And Portfolio Reshaping
summary: Hormel Foods (HRL) is back on investors radar after a busy week, as the company raised its full year 2026 earnings guidance alongside reporting Q1 results and continuing to reshape its portfolio. See our latest analysis for Hormel Foods. At a share price of $24.82, Hormel Foods has seen a 6.11% year to date share price return and a 6.94% 90 day share price return. However, the 1 year total shareholder return of 8.59% and 5 year total shareholder return of 38.30% point to longer term pressure...
